@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

@gameId = 75fcb7a3-04ff-40e0-a063-8d26512ab12c
@playerId = 5eb744c6-f2b7-4d00-a961-a466313e7791
@targetPlayerId = replace-with-target-player-id

###
# Flip7 flows
#
# 1. Create a game.
# 2. Copy the returned gameId into @gameId.
# 3. Call start round.
# 4. If the response includes pendingAction, resolve it with /actions.
# 5. Use /draw or /stay on the current player's turn.
# 6. Repeat until the game ends.
# 7. Use /games/finished and /games/finished/{gameId} to inspect the final result.

### Create game
POST {{baseUrl}}/games
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "playerNames": ["Alice", "Bob"]
}

### Get game by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/games/{{gameId}}

### Start round
POST {{baseUrl}}/games/{{gameId}}/rounds/start

### Draw card
POST {{baseUrl}}/games/{{gameId}}/draw
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "playerId": "{{playerId}}"
}

### Stay
POST {{baseUrl}}/games/{{gameId}}/stay
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "playerId": "{{playerId}}"
}

### Apply pending action
POST {{baseUrl}}/games/{{gameId}}/actions
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "targetPlayerId": "{{targetPlayerId}}"
}

### List finished games
GET {{baseUrl}}/games/finished

### Get finished game detail
GET {{baseUrl}}/games/finished/{{gameId}}

###
# Flow notes
# - startRound deals one card to each player in turn order.
# - If an Action card appears during the opening deal, the deal pauses and you must resolve it with /actions.
# - FREEZE and FLIP_THREE can target any ACTIVE player, including the player who drew the card.
# - SECOND_CHANCE is applied automatically to the player who drew it.
# - When the game is GAME_OVER, only read endpoints should be used.